            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Actually, apparently quite a few other normal mode keystrokes that can silently change the value of `foldenable`, for example `zM` in a buffer with `nofoldenable` will toggle it to `foldenable`, but doesn't trigger `OptionSet` either.\r\n\r\nThis seems to be part of a bigger problem, namely that a _lot_ of places in the C source simply flick options by setting a new value in some C struct and `OptionSet` is never triggered for it. The issue is not limited to folding at all.\r\n\r\nI wonder whether this can be solved at all (with reasonable effort), or if the documentation for `OptionSet` should simply mention that it only reliably fires for `:set` (and maybe script constructs like `let &opt = â€¦`, didn't test that).",
